From 3b4cd3207819d05891f7ca906c013c8ff2859372 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: P Praneesh <ppranees@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Sep 2025 23:12:13 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Upstream:DP:wifi:ath12k: Add multi-user support in RX monitor
 mode

Currently, RX monitor mode in ath12k assumes a single-user context for
PPDU processing. Structures such as hal_rx_mon_ppdu_info contain singular
instances of mpdu_info, msdu_info, and mpdu_q, which limits the ability
to track and process multiple users in UL MU scenarios.

This limitation causes incorrect handling of MPDU and MSDU metadata when
multiple users are involved in a PPDU. Specifically, shared queues and
metadata fields can lead to data corruption, misclassification, and
loss of per-user granularity in monitoring.

To address this, extend hal_rx_mon_ppdu_info to support arrays indexed
by user_id for mpdu_info, msdu_info, and mpdu_q. Update all relevant
parsing, initialization, and processing logic to operate on a per-user
basis. Introduce user_id tracking throughout the RX monitor pipeline to
ensure correct association of TLVs and buffers.

Patch-dependency :
0475-08-Upstream-DP-Add-logic-for-PPDU-based-reaping-for-mon.patch

Signed-off-by: P Praneesh <ppranees@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c      |   5 +
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/hal_mon_cmn.h |   7 +-
 .../net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c   | 125 ++++++++++--------
 .../net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hal_mon.c   |  35 +++--
 4 files changed, 104 insertions(+), 68 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
index b826f9c..1cf3888 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
@@ -1625,6 +1625,8 @@ void ath12k_dp_mon_pdev_rx_attach(struct ath12k_pdev_dp *dp_pdev)
 	struct ath12k_pdev_mon_dp *dp_mon_pdev = dp_pdev->dp_mon_pdev;
 	struct ath12k_mon_data *pmon = &dp_mon_pdev->mon_data;
 	const struct ath12k_dp_arch_mon_ops *mon_ops;
+	struct hal_rx_mon_ppdu_info *ppdu_info = &pmon->mon_ppdu_info;
+	int i;
 
 	skb_queue_head_init(&pmon->rx_status_q);
 
@@ -1643,6 +1645,9 @@ void ath12k_dp_mon_pdev_rx_attach(struct ath12k_pdev_dp *dp_pdev)
 		mon_ops->mon_pdev_rx_mpdu_list_init(pmon);
 
 	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dp_mon_pdev->mon_desc_used_list);
+
+	for (i = 0; i < HAL_MAX_UL_MU_USERS; i++)
+		skb_queue_head_init(&ppdu_info->mpdu_q[i]);
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(ath12k_dp_mon_pdev_rx_attach);
 
